# Vegetable Fried Rice

> A nutritious and versatile dish perfect for a quick dinner or as a side. #vegetarian #side #asian

- Rice | 2 cups | 
- Vegetable Oil | 2 tbsp | 
- Garlic | 2 cloves | 
- Onion | 1 small | 

Heat a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add vegetable oil, then saut√© garlic and onion until the onion starts to become translucent, about 2 minutes.

- Carrot | 1 medium | Diced
- Edamame | Shelled Frozen, 1 cup | Thawed
- Bean Sprouts | 1 cup | 
- Peas | Frozen, 1/2 cup | Thawed

Add diced carrot and cook for another 2-3 minutes. Then, add the cooked edamame, bean sprouts, and thawed peas. Stir-fry for about 2 minutes until the vegetables are tender but still crisp.

- Soy Sauce | 2-3 tbsp | 
- Sesame Oil | 1 tsp | 
- Salt And Pepper | To taste | 

Add the rice to the skillet. Break up any clumps and stir well to combine with the vegetables. Pour the soy sauce and sesame oil over the rice, season with salt and pepper, and stir-fry for 5-7 minutes, or until the rice is heated through and slightly crispy.

- Green Onions | 2 | 
- Egg | 1 | Scrambled, optional
- Sesame Seeds | A sprinkle for garnish | Optional

(Optional) If using, add the scrambled egg, tofu, or both to the rice and mix thoroughly. Finish by garnishing with chopped green onions and a sprinkle of sesame seeds, if desired.
